        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>May 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1830</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Revd Mr. Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Your favour with the<lb/> accompanying Paper came safe to hand.
                I<lb/> read your communication with much pleasure,<lb/> your reply is inanswerable,
                and your quotations<lb/> in support of your opinions pointedly appropriate.<lb/> I
                doubt not your work will be read with<lb/> interest by all denominations.</p>
            <p rend="indent(12)"><persName>Mr. Harrison</persName><lb/> the bookseller who has
                kindly given publicity<lb/> to your circular, informed me that should<lb/> you send
                him a few copies he will dispose<lb/> of them charging you only a commission.
                He<lb/> further states, that many christians would<lb/> purchase who are averse to
                have their names<lb/> attached to a subscription paper. I cannot<lb/> flatter you
                with an account of many<lb/> subscribers, <persName>Nat Hart</persName> your friend
                obtained<lb/> many who could have placed their names<lb/> on my paper. Which by the
                by is just the<lb/> same. I have shown him and others<lb/> your communication in the
                    <placeName>Richmond</placeName> Whig<add>?</add>—<lb/> and they are all highly
                pleased.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>as yet there are only three or four names<lb/> to your circular, as the number will
                be<lb/> small, I shall omit sending you the<lb/> list at the time you mention.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I regret to learn the illness of<lb/>
                <persName>Miss Etting</persName>, I hope she will recover—<lb/> My Respects to all
                Friends and<lb/> accept the wishes of</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Your Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">(In Haste<add>?</add>)</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob De La Motte</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(5)">The <addressee>Revd. Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">per Brig</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Langdon chi<add>?</add>).</p>
        </body>
